programme.title: The Hunt
programme.desc: In this sly satire, a group of elites gather to hunt ordinary Americans for sport. But one of The Hunted fights back against The Hunters leader.

programme.title: Mission: Impossible - Ghost Protocol
programme.desc: Blamed for the terrorist bombing of the Kremlin, IMF operative Ethan Hunt (Tom Cruise) is disavowed along with the rest of the agency when the President initiates Ghost Protocol. Left without any resources or backup, Ethan must find a way to clear his agencys name and prevent another attack. To complicate matters further, Ethan is forced to embark on this mission with a team of fellow IMF fugitives whose personal motives he does not fully know.

programme.title: Fast and Furious Presents: Hobbs and Shaw
programme.desc: Hobbs and Shaw, the trash-talking sworn enemies, must team up to take down a cyber-genetically enhanced anarchist with a bio weapon that threatens the fate of humanity.

programme.title: Death Race
programme.desc: The worlds hunger for extreme sports and reality competitions has grown into reality TV bloodlust. Now, the most extreme racing competition has emerged and its contestants are murderous prisoners. The rules of the Death Race are simple: win five events and youre set free. Lose and youre road kill splashed across the Internet.

programme.title: Snitch
programme.desc: In the fast-paced action thriller, a fathers teenage son is wrongly accused of a drug distribution crime and is looking at a mandatory minimum prison sentence of 10 years. Desperate and determined to rescue his son at all costs, he makes a deal with the US attorney to work as an undercover informant and infiltrate a drug cartel on a dangerous mission risking everything, including his family and his own life.

programme.title: Charlies Angels
programme.desc: When a devious mastermind embroils them in a plot to destroy individual privacy, the Angels, aided by their loyal sidekick Bosley, set out to bring down the bad guys. But when a terrible secret is revealed, it makes the Angels targets for assassination.

programme.title: Charlies Angels: Full Throttle
programme.desc: The Angels, three investigative agents (Barrymore, Diaz and Liu) who work for the Charles Townsend Detective Agency, return for another high-octane series of adventures as they investigate the theft of a database of witness protection profiles, after five of the people on the list are murdered. Theyre aided by a new Bosley (Bernie Mac), in an adventure which pits them against a fallen angel (Moore), their old nemesis, the Thin Man (Glover), and others.

programme.title: The Italian Job
programme.desc: The plan was flawless. The execution was perfect. Charlie Croker pulled off the crime of a lifetime. The one thing that, he didnt plan on was being double-crossed. Now he wants more than the jobs payoff he wants payback.

programme.title: The Fate of the Furious
programme.desc: Now that Dom and Letty are married, Brian and Mia have retired from the game, and the rest of the crew have been exonerated, the globetrotting team has found a semblance of a normal life. But when a mysterious woman seduces Dom into the world of crime he cant seem to escape, they will face trials that will test them as never before. From the shores of Cuba and the streets of New York City to the icy plains off the arctic Barents Sea, our elite force will criss-cross the globe to stop an anarchist from unleashing chaos on the worlds stage, and bring home the man who made them a family.

programme.title: Welcome to the Jungle
programme.desc: Beck is a bounty hunter sent into the treacherous jungles of the Amazon to bring the rebellious Travis back to the States. When Beck and Travis reluctantly join forces to hunt down a priceless treasure, this unlikely team embarks on a pulse-pounding, nonstop thrill ride.

programme.title: Land of the Dead
programme.desc: Packed with more heart-pounding and blood-curdling thrills than any theatre could show, this special unleashes the ultimate vision of George A Romeros latest living-dead shock-fest.

programme.title: Bastille Day
programme.desc: When a reckless CIA agent and a brilliant pickpocket uncover a large-scale conspiracy, they must work together in order to take down a common enemy.

programme.title: 2 Guns
programme.desc: When an attempt to take down a drug cartel blows up in their faces, two undercover operatives are forced to go on the run together, though neither knows that the other is a federal agent. Suddenly, everyone on both sides of the law wants them dead, and their only hope is to trust each other.

programme.title: Jack Reacher
programme.desc: A military cop becomes involved in a deadly game of cat-and-mouse when five people are randomly murdered by a sniper.

programme.title: Fast and Furious
programme.desc: This high-octane action-thriller sees two men go back to the streets where it all began as they blast their way across Los Angeles and through the Mexican desert.

programme.title: Bad Boys 2
programme.desc: Burnett and Lowrey reunite as out-of-control, trash-talking cops. Bullets fly, cars crash, and laughs explode as they pursue a whacked-out drug lord from the streets of Miami to the barrios of Cuba.

programme.title: Dragonheart: Vengeance
programme.desc: Lukas, a young farmer whose family is killed by savage raiders in the countryside, sets out on an epic quest for revenge, forming an unlikely trio with a majestic dragon and a swashbuckling, sword-fighting mercenary, Darius. Helena Bonham Carter voices Siveth, the ice breathing dragon who was once banished from the kingdom for failing to save the kings life. Compelled by the young mans cause, she emerges from hiding, using her fantastical powers on the trios adventurous journey which brings revelations and rewards beyond vengeance. Dragonheart: Vengeance is an exciting action-adventure filled with fantasy and humor that will thrill the entire family.

programme.title: Jurassic Park III
programme.desc: Desperate to find their missing son, Paul and his wife Amanda trick eminent palaeontologist Dr Alan Grant into accompanying them to Isla Sorna. The small team embark on a dangerous task, searching through a deserted island inhabited by ferocious dinosaurs.

programme.title: Hard Kill
programme.desc: A billionaire CEO hires a team of mercenaries to protect a lethal piece of technology when his daughter is kidnapped.

programme.title: The Dark Knight Rises
programme.desc: It has been eight years since Batman vanished into the night, turning, in that instant, from hero to fugitive. Assuming the blame for the death of DA Harvey Dent, the Dark Knight sacrificed everything for what he and Commissioner Gordon both hoped was the greater good. For a time the lie worked, as criminal activity in Gotham City was crushed under the weight of the anti-crime Dent Act. Everything will change with the arrival of a cunning cat burglar with a mysterious agenda. Far more dangerous, however, is the emergence of Bane, a masked terrorist whose ruthless plans for Gotham drive Bruce out of his self-imposed exile. Even if he dons the cape and cowl again, Batman may be no match for Bane.

The epic graphic novel by Frank Miller assaults the screen with the blood, thunder and awe of its ferocious visual style faithfully recreated in an intense film. Retelling the ancient Battle of Thermopylae, it depicts the titanic clash in which King Leonidas and 300 Spartans fought to the death against Xerxes and his massive Persian army.

programme.title: F9: The Fast Saga
programme.desc: The true meaning of family gets tested like never before as Dom Toretto takes the team on a worldwide ride with high-stakes action, old friends and a surprising new foe.

programme.title: Gladiator
programme.desc: Forced into slavery by the corrupt heir to the throne, Roman general Maximus becomes a gladiator. His prowess in the arena leads him to Rome, the Colosseum, and a showdown with the new emperor.

programme.title: Troy
programme.desc: It is the year 1250 BC, during the late Bronze Age. Two emerging nations begin to clash after Paris, the Trojan prince, convinces Helen, Queen of Sparta, to leave her husband Menelaus, and sail with him back to Troy. After Menelaus finds out that his wife was taken by the Trojans, he asks his brother Agamemnon to help him get her back. Agamemnon sees this as an opportunity for power. So they set off for Troy with 1000 ships holding 50,000 Greeks. With the help of Achilles, the Greeks are able to fight the never-before-defeated Trojans, but they come to a stop by Hector, Prince of Troy.

programme.title: 300: Rise of an Empire
programme.desc: Greek general Themistokles of Athens leads the naval charge against invading Persian forces led by mortal-turned-god Xerxes and Artemisia, vengeful commander of the Persian navy.

programme.title: Fast and Furious Presents: Hobbs and Shaw

Lose and youre road kill splashed across the Internet.

programme.title: Snitch
programme.desc: In the fast-paced action thriller, a fathers teenage son is wrongly accused of a drug distribution crime and is looking at a mandatory minimum prison sentence of 10 years. Desperate and determined to rescue his son at all costs, he makes a deal with the US attorney to work as an undercover informant and infiltrate a drug cartel on a dangerous mission risking everything, including his family and his own life.

programme.title: Charlies Angels
programme.desc: When a devious mastermind embroils them in a plot to destroy individual privacy, the Angels, aided by their loyal sidekick Bosley, set out to bring down the bad guys. But when a terrible secret is revealed, it makes the Angels targets for assassination.

programme.title: Charlies Angels: Full Throttle
programme.desc: The Angels, three investigative agents (Barrymore, Diaz and Liu) who work for the Charles Townsend Detective Agency, return for another high-octane series of adventures as they investigate the theft of a database of witness protection profiles, after five of the people on the list are murdered. Theyre aided by a new Bosley (Bernie Mac), in an adventure which pits them against a fallen angel (Moore), their old nemesis, the Thin Man (Glover), and others.

programme.title: The Italian Job
programme.desc: The plan was flawless. The execution was perfect. Charlie Croker pulled off the crime of a lifetime. The one thing that, he didnt plan on was being double-crossed. Now he wants more than the jobs payoff he wants payback.

programme.title: The Fate of the Furious
programme.desc: Now that Dom and Letty are married, Brian and Mia have retired from the game, and the rest of the crew have been exonerated, the globetrotting team has found a semblance of a normal life. But when a mysterious woman seduces Dom into the world of crime he cant seem to escape, they will face trials that will test them as never before. From the shores of Cuba and the streets of New York City to the icy plains off the arctic Barents Sea, our elite force will criss-cross the globe to stop an anarchist from unleashing chaos on the worlds stage, and bring home the man who made them a family.

programme.title: Jack Reacher

programme.title: Dragonheart: Vengeance

Assuming the blame for the death of DA Harvey Dent, the Dark Knight sacrificed everything for what he and Commissioner Gordon both hoped was the greater good. For a time the lie worked, as criminal activity in Gotham City was crushed under the weight of the anti-crime Dent Act. Even if he dons the cape and cowl again, Batman may be no match for Bane.

programme.title: Holmes and Watson

Now these die-hard city dwellers will have to survive the weather, bears, fresh air, and forced time with one another if they want to make it out alive.

As Dusty demonstrates his flair for athletics, home repair and bad-boy charisma, Taggart finds himself in a no-holds-barred battle to one-up his rival and win the approval of his family.

But when the young queen falls gravely ill, a reluctant Dolittle is forced to set sail on an epic adventure to a mythical island in search of a cure, regaining his wit and courage as he crosses old adversaries and discovers wondrous creatures.

Raised by Papa Elf, Buddy comes to realise he doesnt fit in with the other elves. Determined to find a place where he belongs, Buddy searches for his real dad in New York City. In the Big Apple, Buddy finds out why his dad is on the naughty list. But most importantly, he sees that the world is seriously lacking in Christmas spirit, which causes Santa all kinds of problems. So with the help of a beautiful department store elf, Buddy tries to teach his dad and the world the true meaning of Christmas spirit and to prove to everyone that Santa really exists.

programme.desc: Doug tags along with his Dad and Grandbot on their yearly square dancing trip, until a part in their car stops working and they have to search all over a little roadside town to find it. While in town, they discover a bunch of fun new things and decide to make traditions out of their adventure that day./Emma convinces the robots to give playing in the snow a try. But when Bob Bot cant see the fun in it, Emma and Doug try to figure out an activity that he can enjoy.

programme.title: Team Zenko Go
programme.sub-title: Tanakas Moving Castle Zenko Dont Go
programme.desc: Mr. Tanaka is moving places all by himself, so Team Zenko step in to assist, and learn the importance of asking people for help. When Sams skateboard competition falls on the same day as her favourite creator Ken KaBlams comic book signing, TZG secretly prevents him leaving town before she gets the chance to meet him.

programme.title: Gabbys Dollhouse
programme.desc: Gabby receives a special nighttime delivery, unboxing a glow-in-the-dark train engine. However, she realizes that shes missing the other three train cars to complete the whole train. The Gabby Cats help Gabby build the other three glow-in-the-dark train cars by creating shapes through interactive/musical games. In our Gabby Cat of the Day Segment, DJ Catnip sings a song.

programme.title: Not Quite Narwhal
programme.desc: Chef J tells Ollie he cooks with love. Kelp and Ollie set out to make food with love for him. When various food combos fail, Ollie considers giving up, because it isnt good enough. Kelp goes to his Dad for answers, and two seemingly different ingredients form something magical. When Cruz is not his usual upbeat self, Kelp tries various ways to cheer him up before realizing the best way to be a good friend is to just sit with him, and let him feel what hes feeling.

programme.title: Gabbys Dollhouse
programme.desc: With a little help from Gabbys imagination, a sparkly toy banana turns into a magical Rainy Day Banana that helps Gabby and the Gabby Cats have fun on a rainy day! They have silly banana snacks with Cakey, make crafts to tell a story with Baby Box, and have an a-meow-zing banana dance party with DJ Catnip. For our Gabby Cat of the Day segment, Cakey sings a song!

programme.title: Dragons Rescue Riders: Heroes of the Sky
programme.desc: ts the story of twins Dak and Leyla who were rescued from a shipwreck at a very early age by a kindly mother dragon who raised them alongside her own son, Winger. Because they were raised by dragons, Dak and Leyla cannot only ride dragons, they have learned to speak their language and what sounds like growls or roars to anyone else, sound like perfect English to them.Now, these two kids and their five dragon friends pay forward their mothers kindness by rescuing dragons and people.

programme.title: Abominable and the Invisible City
programme.desc: Following the events of the feature, Yi struggles to recreate her violin magic without Everest. While her mom and NaiNai prepare for the grand opening of their family dumpling shop, Yi, Jin, and Peng discover that Yis violin has attracted a magical bird-like creature, Fenghuang, who needs their help. Yis music also calls on Everest, who returns to join the crew and find Fenghuang a suitable home.

programme.title: The Croods: Family Tree
programme.desc: Guy is always surprising Eep with romantic gestures and Eep wants to return the favor. But when Guy proves impossible to surprise, Eep has to step up her game.

programme.title: Boss Baby: Back In Business
programme.desc: When Frederic Estes creates the cutest plushy ever that is the hottest toy in town, the field team must destroy the last remaining one but are powerless against its cuteness.

programme.title: Boss Baby: Back In Business
programme.desc: After Boss Baby allows Gigi to pottytrain him, he realizes being nude might make him a better businessman, but Tim refuses to let that happen.

programme.title: The Epic Tales of Captain Underpants
programme.sub-title: Captain Underpants and the Problematic Pandemonium of the Punishing Plungerina
programme.desc: After helping George and Harold make a comic featuring the heroine Plungerina, Erica asserts that Plungerina could be better that Captain Underpants. Unfortunately, Krupp - and therefore Captain Underpants - is away at a principals convention.Theres no one to save them...until a real life Plungerina saves tthe day! But who is really Plungerina?

programme.title: The Epic Tales of Captain Underpants
programme.sub-title: Captain Underpants and the Bombastic Blathering of Brainy Blabulous
programme.desc: When Krupp transfers to another school, George and Harold follow, only to find a bizarro version of Jerome Horwitz Elementary, where the teachers are nice and the kids are well-behaved. But no ones having any fun! George and Harold want to right this wrong with pranks and comics. But Krupp enlists Mr. Neamer (bizarro Meaner), who then super-enlargers his brain and becomes Brainy Blabulous, in order to stop the subversion of authority.

programme.title: Kung Fu Panda: The Dragon Knight
programme.desc: Po and Blades personalities clash as they track Klaus and Veruca and fight off some of Pos old foes. Meanwhile, Klaus and Veruca continue on their path of destruction while looking for the mysterious "Lotus".

programme.title: Kung Fu Panda: The Dragon Knight
programme.desc: Pos moral lines are blurred when he and Blade have to break an untrustworthy hedgehog monk (Zhen) out of jail to get more information on what Klaus and Veruca stole from the Lotus. programme.title: Jurassic World: Chaos Theory
programme.desc: Darius sets out to capture the dangerous Allosaurus that killed his friend. But he is thrown a curveball when an old friend returns with shocking news.

programme.title: Jurassic World: Chaos Theory

programme.title: Jurassic World: Chaos Theory
programme.desc: Fueled by adrenaline and gas station junk food, Ben and Darius arrive at Sammys ranch only to run into another familiar face: Bumpy! What was supposed to be a reunion among friends quickly becomes a deadly game of cat and mouse.

programme.desc: While the chickens on evil Mrs Tweedys farm dream of a better life, a clever hen named Ginger is hatching plans to fly the coop for good. The only problem is, chickens cant fly or can they? Every escape attempt goes fowl until Rocky, a smooth-talking All-American rooster, crash-lands into the coop. Its hardly poultry in motion when Rocky attempts to teach Ginger and her fine feathered friends to fly but, with teamwork, determination and a little bit of cluck, the fearless flock plots one last daring attempt in a spectacular bid for freedom! Featuring unforgettable characters, incredible animation and all-star voice talent, this instant classic from the academy Award-winning creators of Wallace and Gromit is eggs-traordinary fun for the whole family!

Join Tulio and Miguel and their hilarious horse Altivo as they set sail, map in hand, in search of golden treasure in the all-star adventure, The Road to El Dorado! Upon landing on the shores of El Dorado, the legendary Lost City of Gold, Tulio and Miguel are mistaken for gods and are lavished with riches beyond their wildest dreams! As friendship, loyalty, and greed collide, our unlikely heroes must make the decision of their lives: run off with the gold or face unforeseen dangers to save the people of El Dorado.

programme.title: Migration

programme.title: Mountain Men
programme.desc: There are men in America who must still make their living off the land: hunting and trapping to provide for their families. Their very survival is predicated on utilising ancient skills perfected over many years.

programme.title: American Restoration
programme.desc: Rick Dale, one of Pawn Stars most popular experts, runs Las Vegas based Ricks Restorations, a family business that finds, restores and upcycles cool objects ranging from Cadillacs to Coke Machines. The before and after reveals of his work are always highlights, in part because of the history nuggets Rick Dale shares about each object, whether its a barber chair or a gas pump. In this spinoff series, featuring the dynamic characters at Ricks workplace, viewers will watch a variety of objects be bought, bartered and transformed, learning the process of restoration; how do you duplicate Coke machine red? Where can you find 1920s tires? A storyteller who works with tools instead of a pen, Rick shares when and why objects were invented, who used them and how fixing or transforming them changes their value.

programme.title: High Arctic Haulers
programme.desc: Follow the perilous journey of five crews on cargo ships during a brief window when the Arctic ice recedes and waterways open to allow limited access. Known as the Sealift, the ships are a lifeline for the remote communities up in the Canadian Arctic. From construction materials to new vehicles, modular housing to a years supply of food, these are necessities residents have waited over a year for. High Arctic Haulers is a high-stakes journey at sea where supplies must arrive before winter sets in.

programme.title: The Liquidator
programme.desc: Flea market haggler. Storage locker trader. Pawnshop owner. When it comes to moving discarded merchandise Jeff Schwarz has done it all. Jeff has bought and sold his way up the food chain to become the owner of Direct Liquidation, a 30,000-square-foot warehouse chock full of ever-changing oddities, household goods, and urban artefacts that are going to make him rich. Armed with two cell phones, a wallet full of cash and his razor-sharp negotiating skills, Jeff is on the job seven days a week trying to buy low and sell high and most importantly, keep the goods moving. This program will give you a ringside seat to Jeffs fast-paced, high-stakes, buy-and-sell world. From getting the tip and checking out the goods to making the deal and finding a buyer, youll see it all - and it isnt always pretty.

programme.title: The Amazing Spider-Man
programme.desc: After Peter Parker is bitten by a genetically altered spider, he gains new-found, spider-like powers and ventures out to save the city from the machinations of a mysterious reptilian foe.

programme.title: The Amazing Spider-Man 2
programme.desc: Spider-Mans greatest battle begins when an evil corporation attempts world domination by deploying an army of super villains to crush Peter Parker.

programme.title: Spider-Man: Homecoming
programme.desc: A young Peter Parker/Spider-Man begins to navigate his new-found identity as the web-slinging superhero. Thrilled by his experience with the Avengers, Peter returns home where he lives with his Aunt May, under the watchful eye of his new mentor, Tony Stark. Peter tries to fall back into his normal daily routine - distracted by thoughts of proving himself to be more than just your friendly neighbourhood Spider-Man. But when the Vulture emerges as a new villain, everything that Peter holds most important will be threatened.

programme.title: Spider-Man: No Way Home
programme.desc: With Spider-Mans identity now revealed, Peter asks Doctor Strange for help. When a spell goes wrong, dangerous foes from other worlds start to appear, forcing Peter to discover what it truly means to be Spider-Man.

programme.title: Blade
programme.desc: Before Blades mother gave birth to him, she was bitten by a vampire, which made Blade immune to vampires. Now a vampire hunter, Blade, joined by vampire detective Hannibal King and Dracula-descendent Frank Drake, slay vampires.

programme.title: Morbius
programme.desc: Biochemist Dr Michael Morbius tries to cure himself of a rare blood disease, but he inadvertently infects himself with a form of vampirism instead.

programme.title: Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles (2014)
programme.desc: The city needs heroes. Darkness has settled over New York City as Shredder and his evil Foot Clan have an iron grip on everything from the police to the politicians. The future is grim until four unlikely outcast brothers rise from the sewers and discover their destiny as Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles. The Turtles must work with fearless reporter April ONeil and her wise-cracking cameraman Vern Fenwick to save the city and unravel Shredders diabolical plan.

programme.title: Combat Wombat: Back 2 Back
programme.desc: An evil tech genius threatens to turn the city into a metaverse simulation, leaving the Combat Wombat to save the day.

programme.title: Batman Begins
programme.desc: This story explores the origins of the Batman legend and the Dark Knights emergence as a force for good in Gotham. In the wake of his parents murder, disillusioned industrial heir Bruce Wayne travels the world seeking the means to fight injustice and turn fear against those who prey on the fearful. He returns to Gotham and unveils his alter-ego: Batman, a masked crusader who uses his strength, intellect and an array of high tech deceptions to fight the sinister forces that threaten the city.

programme.title: The Dark Knight
programme.desc: With the help of Lt. Jim Gordon and District Attorney Harvey Dent, Batman sets out to destroy organised crime in Gotham for good. The triumvirate proves effective, but soon find themselves prey to a rising criminal mastermind known as The Joker, who thrusts Gotham into anarchy and forces Batman closer to crossing the fine line between hero and vigilante.

programme.title: The Dark Knight Rises
programme.desc: It has been eight years since Batman vanished into the night, turning, in that instant, from hero to fugitive. Assuming the blame for the death of DA Harvey Dent, the Dark Knight sacrificed everything for what he and Commissioner Gordon both hoped was the greater good. For a time the lie worked, as criminal activity in Gotham City was crushed under the weight of the anti-crime Dent Act. Everything will change with the arrival of a cunning cat burglar with a mysterious agenda. Far more dangerous, however, is the emergence of Bane, a masked terrorist whose ruthless plans for Gotham drive Bruce out of his self-imposed exile. Even if he dons the cape and cowl again, Batman may be no match for Bane.

programme.title: Man of Steel
programme.desc: A young boy learns that he has extraordinary powers and is not of this Earth. As a young man, he journeys to discover where he came from and what he was sent here to do. But the hero in him must emerge if he is to save the world from annihilation and become the symbol of hope for all mankind.

programme.title: Wonder Woman (2017)
programme.desc: Before she was Wonder Woman, she was Diana, princess of the Amazons, trained to be an unconquerable warrior. Raised on a sheltered island paradise, when an American pilot crashes on their shores and tells of a massive conflict raging in the outside world, Diana leaves her home, convinced she can stop the threat. Fighting alongside man in a war to end all wars, Diana will discover her full powers and her true destiny.

programme.title: Wonder Woman 1984
programme.desc: In the vibrant, sleek 1980s, Wonder Woman will have to muster all her strength, wisdom and courage as she finds herself squaring off against Maxwell Lord and the Cheetah.

programme.title: Hulk
programme.desc: Scientist Bruce Banner has anger management issues. His quiet life as a brilliant research scientist working with ex-girlfriend Betty Ross conceals a painful past. A freak lab accident reveals Bruces heroic impulses but also unleashes his inner demons. And he becomes the most powerful being on the face of the Earth: a superhero and a monster.

programme.title: Watchmen: Chapter I
programme.desc: In an alternate world, the murder of a government sponsored superhero draws his outlawed colleagues out of retirement, into a mystery that threatens their lives and the world itself.

programme.title: The Punisher
programme.desc: Undercover FBI agent Frank Castle (Thomas Jane) is crushed when his wife and children are killed after accidentally witnessing a mafia hit. With nothing left to lose or to live for, Castle becomes The Punisher a one-man judge, jury and executioner who declares open season on criminals throughout America. Based on the Marvel Comics character, the film also stars John Travolta, Laura Harring, Samantha Mathis and Rebecca Romijn.

programme.title: Punisher: War Zone
programme.desc: The Punisher is around and trouble begins when he accidentally kills an undercover FBI agent while raiding the warehouse of Mafia warlord Billy the Face, prompting a crisis of conscience in the vigilante. Billy is then fed through a glass recycling machine, creating one of the Punishers greatest comic book enemies, Jigsaw. programme.title: Ryan Defrates: Secret Agent
programme.desc: Ryan Defrates: Secret Agent is an animated action-adventure series about a young spy with a whole lot to learn! Hes arrogant and reckless and always insists on working alone. That is, until the day hes paired with a very unlikely partner his mum! Deb Defrates is not a spy. She knows more about shopping than solving crime, but her wisdom and kindness somehow always seem to save the day.

programme.title: Kids Beach Club
programme.desc: Join the Beach Club Kids as they navigate life, explore character lessons, and have a blast playing memorable games while discovering God through the pages of His Word, the Bible.

programme.title: Soul Sessions
programme.desc: Hosted by Sara Jane Elika Soul Sessions is an exploration into the New Zealand gospel music scene with a focus on Pacific musicians and artists. The award-winning artists are a mix of new and established faces, who share the vision of expressing their faith through music.

programme.title: View and Chew
programme.desc: This show wouldnt be complete without some eats on the street, so grab a seat and take a sneak peek at some sweet treats and tasty meats from West to East.

programme.title: New Creation Church
programme.sub-title: Speak Out By Faith And Win
programme.desc: Pastor Joseph Prince preaches dynamic messages centred on the pure gospel of the grace of God.

programme.title: The Kindness Diaries
programme.desc: Adventurer Leon Logothetis travels from Alaska to Argentina relying on the kindness of strangers and surprising unsuspecting good Samaritans with life-changing gifts!

programme.title: Alaska Missionaries
programme.desc: Real Missionaries, doing real work, helping real people in real remote parts of Alaska. Sit alongside dedicated people of faith giving their all to make a difference in a location filled with breathtaking scenery.

programme.title: Sugarcreek Amish Mysteries
programme.desc: After Cheryls 3-year engagement ends in a devastating breakup, her life is turned upside down when her aunt offers her an escape from Chicago to the Amish town of Sugarcreek. Struggling with being a fish out of water, Cheryl uncovers an unsettling secret that could disrupt the small town of Ohio. As Cheryl begins to solve the mystery, she finds community, belonging and the potential of new love. Will Sugarcreek become Cheryls new home?

programme.title: An American in Austen
programme.desc: Librarian and aspiring novelist Harriet Goodson is struggling with writers block and an overactive imagination fuelled by her favourite novel, Pride and Prejudice. So when her boyfriend Ethan Pronce proposes in a less-than-fairytale fashion, she answers with a hesitant maybe - still holding out hope for her own Mr Darcy moment. But Harriets world is turned upside down when she wakes up inside the pages of Pride and Prejudice itself as the newly arrived American cousin of the Bennet family. Though shes instantly charmed by the famously brooding Mr Darcy, she knows he belongs with Elizabeth Bennet doesnt he? As she navigates the Regency-era world with her 21st-century sensibilities, Harriet begins to question what true romance really looks like - and whether the fantasy shes chasing is getting in the way of her real-life happy ending.

programme.title: Live @ Psalter Studios
programme.sub-title: Anna Weatherup and Eric and Monique
programme.desc: Docu-music series featuring an array of Christian musicians including such artists as Josh Cunningham (The Waifs), Anna Weatherup and Castles In Air, an Indie Rock band from California.

programme.title: Hour of Power
programme.desc: Since 1970 the Hour of Power has been reaching viewers from around the world. Originally founded by Dr Robert H Schuller, the program became the most-watched religious program in the world, reaching 17 million viewers. Now under the leadership of Bobby Schuller, Dr Schullers grandson. The congregation worships at Shepherds Grove Church in Garden Grove, CA. The program aims to provide spiritual principles and practices that can help people, as they become happy students of Jesus and live a life of meaning. To learn more about who they are in Christ through the process of formation, to belong to his family of believers and become a part of the community and to heal as they are loved and then love and help heal others through mission. Jesus Christ ushered in the Kingdom of God into our world through His death and resurrection. He invites everyone to be a part of this amazing movement by trusting and following Him. There is no fuller, richer life than the one that is lived in Christ.

programme.title: Joel Osteen
programme.desc: Direct from Houston, Texas, USA, join Joel and Victoria Osteen and the team from Lakewood Church for this program of powerful music and empowering preaching. Experience from the weekend church service of Lakewood Church, the largest and fastest growing church in America that is inspiring millions of people around the world!

programme.title: Give Me an Answer
programme.sub-title: Was Spinoza an Influencer of Christianity?
programme.desc: Give Me an Answer exists to answer lifes most difficult questions. The shows are recorded on college campus across the United States where Cliffe Knechtle engages with skeptical students and professors, to give real answers to the tough questions about Christianity.

programme.title: Wedding Bells
programme.desc: Nick and Molly, commitment-phobic and busy professionals with little in common, are asked to be the best man and maid of honour at the wedding of their mutual friends, Amy and Jamie. When the wedding is put in danger, they must work together to plan the perfect day. Can they put aside their differences to open their hearts to love?

programme.title: Centuries Collide
programme.sub-title: Martin Luther - The First Viral Post
programme.desc: Millions of things are posted everyday across countless platforms all in hopes of going VIRAL. In this episode learn about Martin Luther the man behind the worlds first VIRAL POST that brought about one of the biggest world-changing events of all time - The Protestant Reformation.

programme.title: The Divine Adventure
programme.desc: Are you looking for Gods best for your life? Do you have a plan for getting there? Deeply practical and intensely personal, The Divine Adventure unpacks twelve powerful spiritual disciplines that will revolutionise your prayer life, deepen your intimacy with God, create balance between rest and work, cultivate meaningful community with others, and more. Drawing from Scripture, ancient writings, visits to holy sites, and her own life experiences of brokenness and breakthrough, Rebecca Friedlander shares the keys that any follower of Christ can use to unlock a life of wonder, passion, and flourishing faith.

programme.title: Smoketown
programme.sub-title: For Those Who Have Eyes To See
programme.desc: In the wake of a mysterious and shocking murder, three unique people - an Assistant Chief of Police, a reporter, and a teenage girl - are empowered to fight for the citys poorest neighbourhood.

programme.title: Life with Paul De Jong
programme.desc: We like to call it soul food. This program uses creative illustration, real life stories and biblical teaching to encourage and help viewers discover a greater purpose to their lives.

programme.title: David Jeremiah
programme.desc: With his respected position in Potiphars house Joseph could have given in to temptation, but because he stayed true to his convictions and loyal to God, he was able to achieve victory over temptation.

programme.title: Planetshakers
programme.desc: Join Planetshakers for their church service in Melbourne. A fresh Word with praise and worship each week. Live empowered.

programme.title: A Very Tall Man
programme.desc: Gary Hoogvliet, a very tall man, interviews interesting folk, not quite as tall as he, but nevertheless with fascinating and inspiring stories to tell.

programme.title: The Last Bridesmaid
programme.desc: Becca is always the bridesmaid, never the bride - and thats fine by her. Focused on her familys business, shes content to let love happen naturally. But when her cousin sets her up with best man Aidan during wedding number ten, Beccas outlook is challenged. Meanwhile, a chance friendship with wedding videographer Kyle, a passionate filmmaker with a different view on love, sparks unexpected chemistry. As Becca balances career ambitions and hidden creative dreams, she and Kyle must navigate their growing feelings - and decide if love is worth the leap.

programme.title: Billy Graham Classics
programme.desc: The best-known Christian evangelist of the 20th century, Billy Graham gained world attention in 1949 with a tent revival in downtown Los Angeles that was scheduled for three weeks and lasted six. In the ensuing 55 years and more, Billy Graham Crusades consistently drew audiences of thousands to arenas and stadiums throughout the world.Classic Crusades presents the best of the last 35 years of Billy Graham that brought the message of salvation through Jesus Christ to the world. World renowned actors, singers, athletes and ministers share the platform with Dr. Graham. Also often features the famous sounds of the Billy Graham Choir, George Beverly Shea and Cliff Barrows for an hour of blessing and inspiration to all who watch.

programme.title: The Wedding Veil
programme.desc: Avery (Chabert), Emma (Reeser) and Tracy (Sweeney) are three close, but far-flung college friends who reunite in different cities every year to go antiquing. During a visit to San Francisco, they discover an extraordinary, antique lace wedding veil with a legend - it is said that whoever possesses the veil will find their true love. The friends agree to purchase the veil together and pass it along to each other to test whether or not the legend is true.

programme.title: Christmas Movie Magic
programme.desc: Alli might get a shot at news reporting if she succeed with her Christmas assignment. Shes to write about the 65 year anniversary of the premiere of the popular seasonal movie Christmas With You. It was filmed in the small town of White Falls, New York, so she heads there to get more facts on the film. In White Falls she meets Brad who runs the old theatre where the film had its world premiere. Undaunted by the obstacles and challenges of her new calling, she rose to become viewed by many as the greatest humanitarian of modern time. Though she herself grew to feel an isolation and an abandonment by God, she said she saw God in every human being. Erik claims his charity is all funded by Santa Claus, so Charitys assignment is to discover where the money really comes from-something other reporters have failed to find out. Knowing this assignment could make or break her career, Charity is initially frustrated that Erik and his associates reveal hardly any information about his mysterious source of funding. But as Charity spends more time with Erik, she begins to appreciate his unwavering conviction that anything is possible if you just believe. programme.title: Born Again - George Whitefield
programme.desc: A documentary feature exploring the life and legacy of George Whitefield. In the 18th century a spiritual and cultural revolution swept across Great Britain and her American colonies. The marvel of this revolution was the son of a Tavern keeper. Out of these humble beginnings came a powerful voice proclaiming the new birth being Born Again. Whitefields voice startled the church like a trumpet blast. His theatrical persuasion transformed the pulpit into sacred theatre. He took the church outdoors and preached to tens of thousands at a time from Moorfields in London to Boston Common in the American colonies. He lifted his voice to preach to the spiritually starving masses and ignited the Evangelical Revival and the First Great Awakening. Whitefield was the most famous man of his time. He crossed the Atlantic 13 times, preached 18 thousand sermons to an estimated 10 million people. He brought about massive social, political, and spiritual transformation in the Transatlantic world with his message .

programme.title: River Cottage to the Core
programme.desc: With all the incredible fruit that is growing in Britain today, Hugh Fearnley-Whittingstall wants to open our eyes to the endless and mouth-watering possibilities at our fingertips. Hugh Fearnley-Whittingstall wants to rip up the cookery rule book to show just how deliciously fruit can enhance and transform meat, fish and pudding dishes, proving it shouldnt be restricted to crumbles, chutneys and pies. Well follow Hugh as he offers his unique take on everything, from savoury strawberries to fruity pizzas. Hell point the finger at the supermarkets quest for cosmetic perfection and shows us how we can grow our own fruit at home that will always taste fantastic, regardless of how it looks. Hugh kicks off the series with the much-anticipated first fruits of the season. To prove that strawberries can be served as a savoury, hes staging a surprising cooking demonstration with strawberry steak and salad recipes, but will his guests buy into it? He also throws a big party to celebrate the reopening of his barn, a year-and-a-half after it was completely destroyed by fire. He also takes to the sea, the hedgerow and the kitchen garden in search of inspiration for the menu. Therell be crackling-covered, fruit-stuffed loins of roast pork, a delicious lemon tart, and aromatic mojitos using unlikely foraged ingredients, including blackberry leaves and lemon balm.

programme.title: Inside the Factory
programme.desc: Gregg Wallace is in Wigan, at an enormous soup factory where they produce 2 million tins a day. He follows the production of vegetable soup, from a pea harvest in Yorkshire right through to the finished soup going into cans and being dispatched. Along the way he watches as a 5 tonne avalanche of peas, around 7 million individual peas, are frozen within 2 hours of being picked. He mixes up 3 tonnes of veg and 500 gallons of tomato sauce and watches as theyre combined and packed into 10 000 tins. Hes astonished by a 27.4 metre tall pressure cooking tower and surprised to learn that for every 1 degree drop in temperature in winter the factory observe a 3.5 percent increase in soup sales.

programme.title: My Dream Home

programme.title: A Place in the Sun
programme.desc: Before they met, John and Liz had separately been visiting the island of Gran Canaria for many years, and five years ago, they were introduced to each other in the town of Puerto Rico.

programme.title: A Place in the Sun
programme.desc: Jill and Chris are dreaming of relocating to the stunning countryside of inland Valencia in Southern Spain. Theyre looking for the perfect property to make their new forever home along with their two beloved dogs, so theyve asked Scarlette Douglas to come to their aid.

programme.title: You Better Watch Out
programme.desc: Aubreys plane is grounded due to a snowstorm, leaving her stranded for the night at a small town airport. She stumbles into the middle of a kidnapping and throws herself into danger as she tries to save the young girl stranded with them.

programme.title: Husband, Father, Killer
programme.desc: Alyssa has a relationship with abusive Steven as a teen, has his child but gives it up for adoption. Years later, their daughter seeks them out, and Steven manipulates her into an affair, neglecting his family.

programme.title: My Sisters Serial Killer Boyfriend
programme.desc: Maddie, a local reporter investigating a series of killings targeting similar looking women is caught off guard when her younger sister Olivia, is attacked in her own home. Urging on the side of caution, Maddie suggests they take a self defence course. When Olivia starts to fall for their instructor, Maddie becomes sceptical when he refuses to reveal anything about himself, and tries to intervene before the relationship turns into a deadly obsession.

programme.title: Single Black Female
programme.desc: Monica is a young host of one of LAs top morning shows. Reeling from the death of her beloved father and the breakup she just suffered, shes ready to focus on moving forward with her life, and channelling all of her energy into getting the new hosting gig on the afternoon talk show at her station. She gets a new assistant, Simone, a beautiful biracial woman who is new in town and so excited to be supporting Monica. They become close quickly, with Simone moving in next door, and engraining herself into Monicas life. But underneath Simones sweet exterior lies a woman who harbors a dark secret, and is determined to become closer than close to Monica, whether she likes it or not! As time goes on, and Simone becomes more and more enmeshed in Monicas life, Monica starts to pick up on the cracks in Simones shiny facade. As she tries to pull back from Simone, Monica and those around her begin to fear that it may be too late - and even worse, that Simone may have had something to do with the death of her father and collapse of her relationship! Monica decides to sever ties with Simone once and for all, however, Simone has other plans. Will Monica get her life back, or will Simone succeed in taking over Monicas life for good?

programme.title: I Wont Let You Go
programme.desc: Inspired by true events. Angela West has always wanted a family, and now that she has one with her devoted husband Keith, she couldnt be happier. When an ex-boyfriend starts stalking her, Angela turns to Keith for protection. But no matter what she tries, she cant seem to shake the stalker who is ruining her life.

programme.title: I Was Octomom
programme.desc: In 2009, Natalie Suleman gives birth to eight children with the help of IVF, only to have her life torn apart, and her identity rebranded by the media.

programme.title: Lust: A Seven Deadly Sins Story
programme.desc: Tiffanie is about to have the wedding of her dreams to her soul mate, the dashing Damon King, founder of King Enterprises. But when Damons old friend Trey arrives, fresh from prison to step in as Damons best man, Tiffanies whole world gets rocked. Sexy and mysterious, Trey triggers a passion in Tiffanie that she never expected, and suddenly the life shes always planned with Damon is uncertain. But Trey still carries wounds from his history with Damon, and his intentions toward both Tiffanie and Damon are not to be trusted.

programme.title: Envy: A Seven Deadly Sins Story
programme.desc: Gabrielle Flores has it all - a devoted husband, a beautiful daughter, and one of the best PR firms in the country. When Gabrielles father suddenly reveals she has a half-sister, Keisha, as a result of a brief affair, only - child Gabrielle is delighted to welcome her into her life. But Keisha, who grew up with nothing, wants more than a sisterly bond from Gabrielle - she wants her life, and is willing to do whatever it takes to get it.

programme.title: Who Is Killing The Cheerleaders?
programme.desc: Ellie, a former cheerleader, returns to her high school as a teacher ten years after she was nearly killed in a series of brutal slayings on the squad. When the attacks start up again shortly after her arrival, she must find the killer before they get to her first.

programme.title: Framed by My Husband
programme.desc: When Junes wealthy husband Rick becomes the target of an extortionist who claims he sexually assaulted her, Rick convinces his wife its an act of revenge by a spurned suitor, and enlists her help to prevent the accusations from going public. June agrees to help him pay off the extortionist, but when the woman is found dead, June becomes the prime suspect.

programme.title: V.C Andrews Pearl In The Mist
programme.desc: Fate whisked Ruby from a simple life in the Louisiana Bayou. But her new riches bring more treachery than happiness. Even after a year as a Dumas, Ruby still wonders at the splendor of the familys New Orleans mansion and rejoices in the love of the father she had never known. But true happiness in her new home is as elusive as the swamp mist. Ruby must carefully avoid her venomous stepmother, Daphne, while making every effort to befriend her twin sister, Gisselle. While attending Greenwood, the exclusive girls boarding school, Ruby doesnt lose hope in a world that never really wanted her. Ruby will have to summon every last ounce of her Cajun strength to reclaim her home, her future, and the happiness she once knew.

programme.title: Beaches
programme.desc: While remaining faithful to the original story, we follow the lifelong friendship between LA-born CC Bloom and San Francisco rich girl Hillary Whitney after they serendipitously meet on Venice Beach. In this update, CC is a budding pop star who is struggling to make it in LA until she is discovered by a music producer who helps her develop her raw talent. Hillary is the daughter of a prominent lawyer who is intent on making her own destiny and getting out from under the control of her domineering father. Their friendship - even with its ups and downs - sustains them for decades, but ends tragically with Hillarys early death.

programme.title: Menendez: Blood Brothers
programme.desc: Erik and Lyle Menendez were educated, nice boys from sunny Beverly Hills, California. Erik was an exceptional tennis player and Lyle was studying at Princeton University. So when their parents were found shot dead in their home, no one could figure out why they would have done it? Everyone was perplexed. Was it for Money? For Fame? The case seemed closed, but that;s when the brothers revealed that they were sexually molested throughout their childhoods by their father, Jose. This was the trial that no one was ready for. Our story follows Erik and Lyle as they struggle with their overwhelming guilt, the harsh reality of abuse, incest and molestation that lead them down this path and the trial that shocked an entire nation of television watchers. Never before seen details emerge as we look closer into the lives of the Menendez brothers.

programme.title: A Roommate to Die For
programme.desc: After a nasty break-up, Faith needs a new roommate to supplement the rent and finds that something very strange is going on with the tenant who decides to move in.

programme.title: Love Triangle Nightmare
programme.desc: Brittany meets a stranger who has everything she wants in a partner and despite being an unknown man as warned by others, she falls in love with him which leads to something tragic.

programme.title: The Night Stalker
programme.desc: Known to many as the "Night Stalker", Richard Ramirez was a cruel and prolific serial killer who murdered 14 people and terrorized Los Angeles in the summer of 1985. This film tells the story of Kit (Bellamy Young), an attorney who travels to San Quentin on an impossible mission to clear the name of Harrison Johnson (Hawthorne James), a death row inmate in Texas whom she believes has been wrongly accused of murders perpetrated by Ramirez (Lou Diamond Phillips). Kit lived in Los Angeles during the fear-tinged summer where Ramirez terrified its citizens and confronting him dredges up old and frightening memories of her own past. As the days count down to the Texas mans execution, Kit confronts Ramirez about his unspeakable crimes in search of an elusive confession, plunging into intense psychological depths in her quest for the truth.

programme.title: Happy Face Killer
programme.desc: Grisly serial killer Keith Hunter Jesperson taunts authorities with scribbled confessions bearing a smiley face at the scenes of his crimes. Based on a true story.

programme.title: Betrayed By Love
programme.desc: Carrie becomes distraught when a car accident takes her sister Rileys life. As the investigation commences, she discovers that the accident might not be the true cause of Rileys death.

programme.title: V.C Andrews Ruby
programme.desc: In the heart of the bayou, Ruby Landry lives a simple, happy life. The only family Ruby Landry has ever known are her loving guardian, Grandmere Catherine, a Cajun spiritual healer, and her drunken, outcast Grandpere Jack. Her life is filled with hope and promise, especially when her attraction for handsome Paul Tate blossoms into a mysterious, wonderful love. But Pauls wealthy parents forbid him to associate with a poor Landry while Grandmere urges her to follow her dream of becoming a great painter. In a faded photograph, Ruby glimpses for the first time the image of her father and learns of a shameful deception and a shocking scheme of blackmail that now must come to light. Stunned by these revelations, she is devastated when Grandmere dies, leaving her to seek out her father in his vast New Orleans mansion. There, in a house of lies, madness, and cruel torment, Ruby clings to her memories of Paul to keep her heart alive. For only their love can save her now.

programme.desc: Emma is a young Amish woman who leads a double life by sneaking out to clubs to flirt and have fun. However, when she accidentally witnesses a murder, her life and community get thrown into peril.

programme.title: An Amish Murder
programme.desc: A woman returns to the Amish farming community of her youth, but her peace is shattered when a murder investigation exposes a dark secret that could destroy her.

programme.title: Cold Blood
programme.desc: Lower Puna, Big Island, Hawaii, is a sun-kissed tropical playground drawing thousands of tourists. But in the shadows lurks another story of drugs, crime, and brutal violence. The two worlds collide on Christmas Eve, 1991, when 23-year-old tourist Dana Ireland takes a bike ride through paradise that ends in tragedy. Hit by a car, raped, and left for dead on a remote trail, Danas murder devastates her family and sends ripples of fear throughout the state. Police investigate a murky world few tourists ever see but come up empty. From the get-go, the police investigation is fraught. The crime scene evidence is messy, forensic technology cant connect the dots, and most suspects or witnesses are either tight-lipped or flat-out lying. When Danas father, furious with the polices lack of results, posts a $28,000 reward for any leads, lowlife tipsters come crawling out of the woodwork and overwhelm police with false information. Lead Detective, Steve Guillermo, is certain of only one fact - a small car struck Danas bike. The search for this vehicle takes over six years but upon finding it, Guillermo starts to untangle the web of lies. Three weeks before a statute of limitations ends on the prime suspects, Guillermo gets a break that closes the case for good.

programme.title: Cold Blood
programme.desc: Lower Puna, Big Island, Hawaii, is a sun-kissed tropical playground drawing thousands of tourists. But in the shadows lurks another story of drugs, crime, and brutal violence. The two worlds collide on Christmas Eve, 1991, when 23-year-old tourist Dana Ireland takes a bike ride through paradise that ends in tragedy. Hit by a car, raped, and left for dead on a remote trail, Danas murder devastates her family and sends ripples of fear throughout the state. Police investigate a murky world few tourists ever see but come up empty. From the get-go, the police investigation is fraught. The crime scene evidence is messy, forensic technology cant connect the dots, and most suspects or witnesses are either tight-lipped or flat-out lying. When Danas father, furious with the polices lack of results, posts a $28,000 reward for any leads, lowlife tipsters come crawling out of the woodwork and overwhelm police with false information. Lead Detective, Steve Guillermo, is certain of only one fact - a small car struck Danas bike. The search for this vehicle takes over six years but upon finding it, Guillermo starts to untangle the web of lies. Three weeks before a statute of limitations ends on the prime suspects, Guillermo gets a break that closes the case for good.

programme.title: Walking Through History
programme.sub-title: Englands Last Battle: The West Country
programme.desc: Appealing to history buffs and dedicated ramblers alike, Sir Tony Robinson embarks on spectacular walks through some of Britains most historic landscapes in search of the richest stories from Britains past. In each programme, Tony follows a bespoke route that allows him to explore on foot both the history of a particularly colourful historical period or event, and the spectacular landscape in which those events unfolded. The walks are proper expeditions with each one taking Tony several days. With various experts he encounters on the way, Tony reveals and discovers places and their hidden stories that ordinary walkers and ramblers might otherwise miss. And, as well as the history, Tony infuses each walk with an appreciation of some of the striking landscapes and geographical features Britain contains.

programme.title: The Crusaders: Fortresses of Faith
programme.desc: At the end of the 11th century, the armies of the First Crusade descended on the Middle East. After the capture of Jerusalem in 1099, they controlled a Christian territory with shifting borders that they defended until 1291. In order to protect themselves, they built the largest and strongest fortresses ever constructed at the time.

programme.title: Time Team
programme.sub-title: Seven Buckets And A Buckle, Breamore Hampshire
programme.desc: One of the richest digs the team has ever undertaken heralds the end of the series. Investigating what is believed to be a Bronze Age barrow in the New Forest, Tony Robinson and the team uncover a Saxon cemetery with a startling array of grave goods, spears, shields, jewellery and a collection of rare buckets unique in Britain.

programme.title: Griffs Great Australian Rail Trip
programme.desc: The first of two parts aboard the legendary Indian Pacific, Griff journeys from Perth to Kalgoorlie, exploring the states riches, and perhaps most curiously - what is a sandgroper?

programme.title: Fortress Britain
programme.desc: The story of William the Conquerors journey from invader to ruler of England. Alice discovers who the Normans really were, Danielle gets some 11th-century battlefield experience.

programme.title: Amazing Engineering: Templar Castles
programme.desc: In Jerusalem, in 1120, the most fascinating and mysterious religious and military order of the Middle Ages was born: The Templars. These brother knights who stemmed from several European countries quickly spread and their convents soon became a vast network stretching from Portugal to Poland, from Scotland to Sicily, and, in the East newly conquered by the Crusaders, from Antioch to Gaza.

programme.title: Beyond Skinwalker Ranch
programme.desc: Andy and Paul return to Bradshaw Ranch in Sedona, Arizona, in search of a rumoured secret military base - and find themselves in a situation that could jeopardise the entire Beyond Skinwalker mission.

programme.title: The UnXplained
programme.desc: According to the Greek philosopher Plato, the lost continent of Atlantis was once home to an advanced civilization before it was destroyed in a cataclysm. But was Platos story merely a myth? Or did Atlantis really exist? For centuries, archaeologists have tried to uncover evidence to prove that this legend is true. Will Atlantis finally be re-discovered, perhaps by employing modern technology? Or will this lost civilization remain unexplained?

programme.title: Historys Raiders
programme.desc: On the night of November 11, 1940, 21 biplanes from a Royal Navy aircraft carrier launched a surprise attack on the Italian fleet anchored in Tarantos port. The Italian ships, thought to be virtually immune to air attack, were protected by anti-torpedo nets, and surrounded by barrage balloons and anti-aircraft defences. But, in less than two hours, the lumbering Swordfish torpedo bombers were able to sink or disable three battleships and several cruisers, and severely damage port installations.

programme.title: Dogfights
programme.desc: In the fighter pilot business, they say speed is life. Speed means the ability to maneuver. Speed is the initiative in a dogfight, with the speed advantage you can almost always outperform and out think your opponent. From the era of piston-driven, prop planes like the F4U Corsair to high-performance jets like the F-86 Sabre and the F4 Phantom, the pursuit of greater speed has defined the development of aircraft.

programme.title: World War II in HD Colour
programme.desc: In 1944 America and Britain in the west and Russia in the east began to close their pincer around Germany. But even now, the outcome was in the balance. The film explores the Allied disaster at Arnhem and the tragedy of the Warsaw uprising, when Polish freedom fighters were abandoned to their fate by Stalin. It tells the shocking story of the liberation of the death camps, when the full extent of the Holocaust became clear for the first time. The film ends with Hitlers last great gamble, as he threw all his last reserves against the oncoming Allied forces in the Ardennes. Conventional wisdom has recently changed as more and more secrets have been revealed particularly in the last five to 10 years, when documents, files and photographs have been released. Code-breaking revelations and newly released government papers on both sides of the Atlantic have added a very insightful new dimension to the understanding of this, the worlds greatest ever conflict. With the very latest satellite-delivered terrain mapping and state-of-the-art graphics, this story can now be told with the very latest access to information which was not previously available.

programme.title: Nazi Hunters
programme.desc: Examines the hunt for Joseph Mengele, a man who experimented on adults and children in the Auschwitz death camps. He was a prime target and was, for many years, the worlds most wanted criminal.

programme.title: The Last Journey of the Vikings
programme.sub-title: The Last Battle Of The Vikings
programme.desc: The year is 1066 and the Vikings are no longer involved in coastal raids or pillaging monasteries but in a power struggle for the throne of England. And it is the Norman duke William who decides that he will be the one to conquer the island.

programme.title: Ancient Apocalypse

programme.title: A Mediterranean Military Jewel

programme.title: The Big Steam Adventure

programme.title: The World from Above

programme.title: The World from Above

programme.title: Walking Through History
programme.sub-title: Englands Last Battle: The West Country
programme.desc: Appealing to history buffs and dedicated ramblers alike, Sir Tony Robinson embarks on spectacular walks through some of Britains most historic landscapes in search of the richest stories from Britains past. In each programme, Tony follows a bespoke route that allows him to explore on foot both the history of a particularly colourful historical period or event, and the spectacular landscape in which those events unfolded. The walks are proper expeditions with each one taking Tony several days. With various experts he encounters on the way, Tony reveals and discovers places and their hidden stories that ordinary walkers and ramblers might otherwise miss. And, as well as the history, Tony infuses each walk with an appreciation of some of the striking landscapes and geographical features Britain contains.

programme.title: The Crusaders: Fortresses of Faith
programme.desc: At the end of the 11th century, the armies of the First Crusade descended on the Middle East. After the capture of Jerusalem in 1099, they controlled a Christian territory with shifting borders that they defended until 1291. In order to protect themselves, they built the largest and strongest fortresses ever constructed at the time.

programme.title: Time Team
programme.sub-title: Seven Buckets And A Buckle, Breamore Hampshire
programme.desc: One of the richest digs the team has ever undertaken heralds the end of the series. Investigating what is believed to be a Bronze Age barrow in the New Forest, Tony Robinson and the team uncover a Saxon cemetery with a startling array of grave goods, spears, shields, jewellery and a collection of rare buckets unique in Britain.

programme.title: Griffs Great Australian Rail Trip
programme.desc: The first of two parts aboard the legendary Indian Pacific, Griff journeys from Perth to Kalgoorlie, exploring the states riches, and perhaps most curiously - what is a sandgroper?

programme.title: Fortress Britain
programme.desc: The story of William the Conquerors journey from invader to ruler of England. Alice discovers who the Normans really were, Danielle gets some 11th-century battlefield experience.

programme.title: Amazing Engineering: Templar Castles
programme.desc: In Jerusalem, in 1120, the most fascinating and mysterious religious and military order of the Middle Ages was born: The Templars. These brother knights who stemmed from several European countries quickly spread and their convents soon became a vast network stretching from Portugal to Poland, from Scotland to Sicily, and, in the East newly conquered by the Crusaders, from Antioch to Gaza.

programme.title: Beyond Skinwalker Ranch
programme.desc: Andy and Paul return to Bradshaw Ranch in Sedona, Arizona, in search of a rumoured secret military base - and find themselves in a situation that could jeopardise the entire Beyond Skinwalker mission.

programme.title: The UnXplained
programme.desc: According to the Greek philosopher Plato, the lost continent of Atlantis was once home to an advanced civilization before it was destroyed in a cataclysm. But was Platos story merely a myth? Or did Atlantis really exist? For centuries, archaeologists have tried to uncover evidence to prove that this legend is true. Will Atlantis finally be re-discovered, perhaps by employing modern technology? Or will this lost civilization remain unexplained?

programme.title: The Australian SAS: The Untold History

programme.title: Close Calls: On Camera
programme.desc: Presented by Nick Knowles, this series brings to life the stories of ordinary people who have faced extraordinary circumstances - emergencies, accidents and incidents. With access to a variety of sources such as video and phone footage shot by the victims and onlookers, dramatic real-life 999 calls, and first-hand accounts from the victims and their friends and families, Close Calls: On Camera relives the split-second moments when everyday events are transformed into disasters and meets the people who lived to tell the tale. Watch the terrifying moment that a mother and her two children are suddenly faced with a life-threatening decision when their car starts burning uncontrollably in a Safari Park lion enclosure, or witness when a day of skiing takes a terrifying turn for three friends, after one of them misjudges the track and disappears into a bottomless crack in the ice.

For the Bennet sisters many trials and tribulations stand between them and their happiness, including class, gossip and scandal.
